lines.text: you think we look pretty good together.
you think my shoes are made of leather
but i'm a substitute for a 'nother guy
i look pretty tall but my heels are high
the simple things ya' see are all complicated
i look pretty young but i'm just backdated yeah
substitute your lies for fact.
i see right through your plastic mac
i look all white but my dad was black
my fine lookin' suit's really made out of sack
i was born with a plastic spoon in my mouth
the north side of my town faced east and the east was facing south.
and now you dare to look me in the eye
those crocodile tears are what you cry.
it's a genuine problem. you won't try
to work it out at all; you just pass it by, pass it by
substitute me for him
substitute. my coke for gin.
substitute. you for my mum.
at least i'll get my washing done
